{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/networkmode"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"The network configuration mode for a virtual machine.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/Se","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/SE","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/SQ","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/SH","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/s16SendableMetatypeP"],"type":"conformsTo"}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"NetworkMode"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each mode maps to a specific "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Virtualization.framework"},{"type":"text","text":" network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"device attachment type. The mode determines how the guest’s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"network traffic is routed relative to the host and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"external network."}]},{"text":"Choosing a Network Mode","type":"heading","anchor":"Choosing-a-Network-Mode","level":2},{"type":"table","header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Mode"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Guest → Internet"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Host → Guest"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Entitlement"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/nat"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✓"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Via resolved IP"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"None"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/bridged(interface:)"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✓"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Own LAN IP"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"com.apple.vm.networking"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✗"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✗"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"None"}]}]]]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For host-guest communication without full network access,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated"},{"type":"text","text":" mode and communicate via the VirtIO socket"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"device ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZVirtioSocketDeviceConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":"), which is always"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attached regardless of network mode."}]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Bridged mode requires the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"com.apple.vm.networking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"restricted entitlement, which must be requested from Apple"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Developer Technical Support."}]}]},{"text":"Why There Is No Host-Only Mode","type":"heading","anchor":"Why-There-Is-No-Host-Only-Mode","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework provides three network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attachment types: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZNATNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZBridgedNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZFileHandleNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":". None of these"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implements host-only semantics directly."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A host-only mode would require a user-space virtual network"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"switch built on top of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZFileHandleNetworkDeviceAttachment"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"handling raw Ethernet frames, DHCP, and packet routing — a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"substantial subsystem that would need its own lifecycle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"management and security hardening. Rather than ship a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"half-baked implementation or silently fall back to NAT"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(which would give VMs unintended internet access), this enum"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only exposes modes that the Virtualization framework supports"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"natively."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need isolated host-guest communication, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with the VirtIO socket device. If you need full IP networking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"between VMs, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/bridged(interface:)"},{"type":"text","text":" on a dedicated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"host-only network interface."}]}]}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Enumeration-Cases","title":"Enumeration Cases","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/bridged(interface:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/isolated","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/nat"],"generated":true},{"anchor":"Initializers","title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/init(from:)"],"generated":true},{"anchor":"Default-Implementations","title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode\/Equatable-Implementations"],"generated":true}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"role":"symbol","title":"NetworkMode","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit11NetworkModeO","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"NetworkMode"}],"roleHeading":"Enumeration","symbolKind":"enum","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"NetworkMode","kind":"identifier"}]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode"},"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/s8SendableP":{"type":"unresolvable","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/s8SendableP","title":"Swift.Sendable"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/Se":{"